hero.title: Hi, I'm Natasha!
hero.des0: I'm a 2nd year computer science specializing in SWE, AI, and business at the University of Xi'an JiaoTong Liverpool.
hero.des1: I love collaborating in teams to create high-quality and sophisticated software.
hero.des2: I build mostly in TS, Python, and Java with strong competences in React, Node, and SQL dbs, though I'm always excited to flex my other muscles.
hero.des3: Currently based in China, but always down to connect, collaborate, and dive into exciting projects.

projects.title: Projects
projects.description: Here are some of my favourite projects I've lead and developed. Not only were they super fun to code, but many of them are providing utilty to real people today!

msmr.subtitle: Quiz Application
msmr.description: Built with Java Swing, this interactive quiz app features a leaderboard to track high scores, enhancing engagement and competition.

uwcribs.subtitle: Dog Tinder App Landing page
uwcribs.description: Designed and developed a sleek, user-friendly landing page for a dating app, optimizing visual appeal and usability

squiggles.subtitle: Note-Taking App
squiggles.description: A simple yet effective note-taking app, actively used by my close friends and me for organizing thoughts and tasks.

skills.title: Skills
skills.description: Though I'm always excited to use the latest and greatest technologies, these are my tried and tested go to tools when building any project.

experience.title: Experience
experience.description: I've had the honour of working at these amazing companies. Hopefully your company will be there too.
